race.comment: TRUCK STOP HONEY (9) was a big maiden winner here in the spring, and she has been holding her form nicely since then. She can make full use of the pole position and is sure to be among the hardest to beat again. TREASURER (2) has not won for some time, but this field is not as strong as some of his recent assignments. Justin Huxtable in the saddle is a bonus, and the pair merits healthy respect. Each way. HAYAKU (3) was beaten by a wide draw at the Gold Coast nearly 2 weeks ago, and has a good record when racing on this circuit. He is peaking at the right time, and this level, a form reversal, is on the cards. SHOW ME THE STARS (6) is capable of better than her recent form suggests, and she is another who is worth including in all combinations to be safe. MISHANI PERSUASION (1) sat close to the pace and fought on gamely to finish runner-up at Chinchilla nearly 3 weeks ago. He benefits from a 3kg claim, and gets a chance to improve his modest track stats. Stick with him.
